018, the Rhodes Scholarship was reinstated for Singapore.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rhodeshouse.ox.ac.uk/news-events/latest-news/news/2018/january/reinstatement-of-the-rhodes-scholarship-for-singapore-in-partnership-with-aps-asset-management/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=1 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180401214130/https://www.rhodeshouse.ox.ac.uk/news-events/latest-news/news/2018/january/reinstatement-of-the-rhodes-scholarship-for-singapore-in-partnership-with-aps-asset-management/ |archive-date=1 April 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref> Different constituencies have been suspended or removed from the scholarship scheme for different reasons, according to the guidelines of the will and the decisions of the trustees.}}|| [[Hertford College, Oxford|Hertford]] || 1939 || [[Prime Minister of Malta]], 1955\u20131957 & 1971\u20131984\n|-\n|{{sortname|Jack|Davis|Jack Davis (Canadian politician)}}||[[University of British Columbia|British Columbia]] || [[St John's College, Oxford|St John's]] || 1939 || Canadian Minister of the Environment (1968\u20131974), B.C. Minister of Energy, Mines and Petroleum Resources (1986\u20131991)\n\n<!-- ==1940s== ----------------------------------------------------------------------- -->\n|-\n| {{sortname|Ossie|Newton-Thompson}} ||[[University of Cape Town|Cape Town]]|| [[Trinity College, Oxford|Trinity]] || 1940 || Member of South African parliament and England [[rugby union]] international\n|-\n| {{sortname|Alan|Stewart|Alan Stewart (educator)}} || [[Massey University|Massey]] || [[University College, Oxford|University]] || 1940 || New Zealand educator and university administrator\n|-\n| {{sortname|Zelman|Cowen}} ||[[University of Melbourne|Melbourne]]|| [[New College, Oxford|New College]] || 1941 || Australian jurist and academic, [[Governor General of Australia]] (1977\u20131982)\n|-\n|{{sortname|Edwin| Busuttil}} || || [[Christ Church, Oxford|Christ Church]] || 1942\n| Speaker of the Maltese House of Repr