ull}} || [[University of Sydney|Sydney]] || [[Brasenose College, Oxford|Brasenose]] || 1978 || 29th [[Prime Minister of Australia]], 2015\u20132018\n|-\n|{{sortname|David |Naylor|C. David Naylor}} ||[[University of Toronto|Toronto]] || [[Hertford College, Oxford|Hertford]] || 1979 || Canadian medical researcher, president of the [[University of Toronto]]\n|-\n|{{sortname|Nancy-Ann Min |DeParle}} || [[University of Tennessee|Tennessee]] <!--and [[Harvard Law School|Harvard]] Her Harvard degree is from the law school, not an undergraduate college.--> || [[Balliol College, Oxford|Balliol]] || 1979 || Administrator of the U.S. Health Care Financing Administration, 1997\u20132000, director of White House Office of Health Reform, 2009\u2013\n|-Pop\n|{{sortname|Stephen|Gumley}} || [[University of Tasmania|Tasmania]] || [[St Catherine's College, Oxford|St Catherine's]] || 1979 || chief executive officer of the [[Defence Materiel Organisation]] (Australia)\n|-\n|{{sortname|Robert|Maloney|Robert Maloney (doctor)}}||[[Harvard College|Harvard]] || [[Magdalen College, Oxford|Magdalen]] || 1979 || Ophthalmologist, [[LASIK]] specialist, ''[[Extreme Makeover]]'' ophthalmologist\n|-\n|[[Marc Tessier-Lavigne]]\n|[[McGill University]]\n|[[New College, Oxford|New College]]\n|1980\n|Canadian [[neuroscientist]], president of [[Stanford University]], past president of [[Rockefeller University]]<!-- ==1980s== ----------------------------------------------------------------------- -->\n|-\n| {{sortname|John|MacBain}} || [[McGill University|McGill]] || [[Wadham College, Oxford|Wadham]] || 1980 || Canadian multi-billionaire, president and CEO of [[Trader Classified Media]], one of the world's largest classified advertising companies\n|-\n| {{sortname|Don|Elder}} || [[University of Canterbury|Canterbury]] || [[Wolfson College, Oxford|Wolfson]] || 1980 || New Zealand engineer and businessman\n|-\n|{{sortname|Clark |Ervin}} ||[[Harvard College|Harvard]] || [[St Catherine's College, Oxford|St Cat