en College, Oxford|Magdalen]]  || 2012 || American human rights activist , senior foreign policy official in the [[Obama administration]], [[U.S. State Department]] special adviser on global youth issues and Pulitzer Price-winning journalist\n|-\n|{{sort name|Shamma|Al Mazrui}} || [[New York University Abu Dhabi]] || || 2014|| [[United Arab Emirates]] Minister of Youth\n|-\n|{{sortname|Yifan|Hou}}||[[Peking University]]||[[Blavatnik_School_of_Government|Blavatnik]]|| 2018<ref>https://www.rhodeshouse.ox.ac.uk/scholars/rhodes-scholars-class-of-2018/yifan-hou/</ref> ||Former womens' world champion of chess\n|-\n|{{sort name|Madison|Tung}} || [[U.S. Air Force Academy]] || [[Oriel College, Oxford|Oriel]] || 2019 || First female wrestler and wrestling national champion at the [[U.S. Air Force Academy]]<ref name=\"winmagazinetung\">{{cite web |last1=Finn |first1=Mike |title=Rhodes Scholar Tung builds off her wrestling drive |url=https://www.win-magazine.com/2019/05/rhodes-scholar-tung-builds-off-her-wrestling-drive/ |website=WIN Magazine: Wrestling News |publisher=Wrestling Insider |accessdate=13 June 2019 |date=28 May 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{sortname|Bruce|Reed|Bruce Reed (political operative)}}\n|[[Princeton University|Princeton]]\n|Lincoln\n|1982\n|Former Chief of Staff to Vice President Joe Biden\n|-\n|{{sortname|Gina|Raimondo}}\n|[[Harvard University|Harvard]]\n|[[New College, Oxford|New College]]\n|1993\n|2014 elected Democratic Governor of [[Rhode Island]]\n|-\n|{{sortname|Andy|Kim|Andy Kim (politician)}}\n|[[University of Chicago]]\n|[[Magdalen College, Oxford|Magdalen]]\n|2005\n|Democratic U.S. Representative for New Jersey's 3rd Congressional District\n<!--|-\n|{{sortname|Hana|Kim}}\n|[[Princeton University|Princeton]]\n|[[Magdalen College, Oxford|Magdalen]]\n|2020\n|Daughter of Andy Kim redlinked -->\n|- \n|{{sortname|Jim|Cooper}}\n|[[University of North Carolina]]\n|[[Oriel College, Oxford|Oriel]]\n|1975\n|U.S. Congressman from Tennessee's 5th Congressional Distri