elers Group\n\n<!-- ==1960s== ----------------------------------------------------------------------- -->\n|-\n|{{sortname|Shahid Javed |Burki}} || [[Government College University, Lahore|Government College]] || [[Christ Church, Oxford|Christ Church]] || 1960 || Economist, [[Finance Minister of Pakistan]] \n|-\n|{{sortname|Richard F. |Celeste}} ||[[Yale]] || [[Exeter College, Oxford|Exeter]] || 1960 || [[Governor of Ohio]] (1983\u20131991), director of the Peace Corps, U.S. Ambassador to India, president of Colorado College\n|-\n|{{sortname|Girish |Karnad}} ||[[Karnatak University|Karnatak]] || [[Lincoln College, Oxford|Lincoln]] and [[Magdalen College, Oxford|Magdalen]] || 1960 || Indian Kannada-language playwright, film actor and director, screenwriter \n|-\n|{{sortname|Lester C. |Thurow}} ||[[Williams College|Williams]] || [[Balliol College, Oxford|Balliol]] || 1960 || American economist and author, professor of economics at MIT\n<!-- |-\n|{{sortname|Paul B. |Van Buren}} -- redlink -- ||[[University of South Dakota|South Dakota]] || [[University College, Oxford|University]] || 1960 || A principal attorney for [[Pacific Telesis]] Group during the [[Bell System divestiture|breakup of the Bell System]], former chairman of The University of South Dakota Foundation -->\n|-\n|{{sortname|Davis|Earle}} ||[[University of British Columbia|UBC]] ||  || 1960 || Canadian physicist\n|-\n|{{sortname|David |Souter}} || [[Harvard College|Harvard]] || [[Magdalen College, Oxford|Magdalen]] || 1961 || Associate Justice of the U.S. Supreme Court, 1990\u20132009\n|-\n|{{sortname|Andrew |Graham|Andrew Graham (academic)}} || [[St Edmund Hall|Oxford]] || [[St Edmund Hall, Oxford|St Edmund]] || 1961 || Political economist, director of the Scott Trust, senior fellow of Oxford Internet Institute, acting master of Balliol College, Oxford, 1997\u20132001, policy advisor to Harold Wilson, 1974\u201376\n|-\n|{{sortname|Rex |Adams}} ||[[Duke University|Duke]] || [[Merton College, Oxford|Merton]]