|Himes}} || [[Harvard College|Harvard]] || [[St Edmund Hall, Oxford|St Edmund]] || 1988 ||  American businessman, Democratic U.S. Representative for Connecticut's 4th Congressional District\n|-\n|{{sortname|Brad|Carson}} ||[[Baylor University|Baylor]] || [[Trinity College, Oxford|Trinity]] || 1989 || U.S. Congressman (Oklahoma), 2001\u20132005\n|-\n|[[Michael McCullough (entrepreneur)|Michael McCullough]]\n|[[Stanford University|Stanford]]\n|[[Balliol College, Oxford|Balliol]]\n|1989\n|Social entrepreneur; founder of [[QuestBridge]], medical investor and entrepreneur, physician, assistant professor at [[University of California, San Francisco|UCSF]]\n|-\n|{{sortname|Tara|Welch}} ||[[University of Southern California]] || [[Corpus Christi College, Oxford|Corpus Christi College]] || 1989 || [[University of Kansas]] [[classics]] professor\n\n<!-- ==1990s== ----------------------------------------------------------------------- -->\n|-\n|{{sortname|Michael|Szonyi}} ||[[University of Toronto|Toronto]] || [[Merton College, Oxford|Merton]] || 1990 || Professor of Chinese history at [[Harvard University]]\n|-\n|{{sortname|Arthur|Mutambara}} ||[[University of Zimbabwe|Zimbabwe]] || [[Merton College, Oxford|Merton]] || 1991 || Zimbabwean politician who became president of one faction of the [[Movement for Democratic Change \u2013 Mutambara|Movement for Democratic Change]] in 2006\n|-\n|{{sortname|David|Coleman|dab=education}} ||[[Yale]] || [[University College, Oxford|University]] || 1991 || Ninth president of the [[College Board]]\n|-\n|{{sortname|Jeff|Shesol}} ||[[Brown University|Brown]] || [[Magdalen College, Oxford|Magdalen]] || 1991 || Author, speechwriter, political cartoonist\n|-\n|{{sortname|Neel|Mukherjee (writer)}} ||[[Jadavpur University|Jadavpur]] || [[University College, Oxford|University]] || 1992 || Novelist, longlisted for the 2014 [[Man Booker Prize]]\n|-\n|{{sortname|Cory|Booker}} ||[[Stanford University|Stanford]] || [[Queen's College, Oxford|Queen's]] || 